            "end_offset": 10447,
            "annotation_id": "PK_140"
        },
        {
            "decision": "You may shower starting five (5) days after surgery, but no tub baths or swimming for at least four (4) weeks. ",
            "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution",
            "start_offset": 10449,
            "end_offset": 10558,
            "annotation_id": "PK_141"
        },
        {
            "decision": "No dressing is needed if wound continues to be non-draining. Any stitches or staples that need to be removed will be taken out by the visiting nurse (VNA) or rehab facility two weeks after your surgery. ",
            "category": "Category 9: Advice and precaution",
            "start_offset": 10560,
            "end_offset": 10761,
            "annotation_id": "PK_142"
        },
        {
            "decision": "7. Please call your surgeon's office to schedule or confirm your follow-up appointment in four (4) weeks.",
            "category": "Category 1: Contact related",
            "start_offset": 10764,
            "end_offset": 10868,
            "annotation_id": "PK_143"
        },
        {
            "decision": "8. Please DO NOT take any non-steroidal anti-inflammatory medications (NSAIDs such as celebrex, ibuprofen, advil, aleve, motrin, etc).",
            "category": "Category 5: Drug related",
            "start_offset": 10871,
            "end_offset": 11003,
            "annotation_id": "PK_144"
        },
        {
